item.title: Keely add a quote by Jennifer Egan
item.description: "I can't tell if she's actually real, or if she's stopped caring if she's real or not. Or is not caring what makes a person real?" -- Jennifer Egan

item.title: Keely add a quote by Jennifer Egan
item.description: "If I had a view like this to look down on every day, I would have the energy and inspiration to conquer the world. The trouble is, when you most need such a view, no one gives it to you." -- Jennifer Egan

item.title: Keely add a quote by Jennifer Egan
item.description: "I'm always happy," Sasha said. "Sometimes I just forget." -- Jennifer Egan

item.title: Keely add a quote by Jennifer Egan
item.description: "A bit of theory as we settle down for lunch: the waiter's treatment of Kitty is actually a kind of sandwich, with the bottom bread being the bored and slightly effete way he normally acts with customers, the middle being the crazed and abnormal way he feels around this famous nineteen-year-old girl, and the top bread being his attempt to contain and conceal this alien middle layer with some mode of behavior that at least approximates the bottom layer of boredom and effeteness that is his norm." -- Jennifer Egan

item.title: Keely add a quote by Jennifer Egan
item.description: "What he needed was to find fifty more people like him, who had stopped being themselves without realizing it." -- Jennifer Egan
